  <data name="FullDescription" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A data store flagged as holding log or audit data (StoresLogData = Yes) should be signed so that records cannot be altered or deleted without detection. When it is not signed, an attacker can tamper with the log and repudiate the events it is meant to prove.

This rule is violated for any storage element whose StoresLogData property is Yes and whose Signed property is not Yes.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="HelpText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Sign or seal log records (for example with an append-only store, a hash chain, or a message authentication code), protect the signing key, and set the store's Signed property to Yes.

If the element does not actually hold log or audit data, correct the StoresLogData property so the diagram reflects reality.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="MessageText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Data store [{0}] holds log or audit data but is not signed, allowing tampering and repudiation of recorded events.</value>
  </data>
